text.tspan: Number of tracked objects in low Earth orbit, by type
Objects are subtracted from the time series after they have reentered the Earth's atmosphere. Not all
objects are tracked: in 2021, the European Space Agency estimated there were more than 130 million
space debris objects larger than 1 millimeter.
Data source: United States Space Force (2023)
Note: Low Earth orbit is defined by a point of closest approach to Earth below 2,000 kilometers. Debris are assigned to the launch date
of the original object from which they were separated.
